The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons has revealed the identities of some convicted sex offenders in Nigeria. rapists in Nigeria The identities of convicted sex offenders in Nigeria have been unveiled by The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons. The action of NAPTIP became necessary following the increasing rape incidents in Nigeria in recent times. It also further reminds Nigerians that the Nigeria Sex Offender Register is still very much active. Below are the identities of some convicted rapists in Nigeria: Nigeria Sex Offender Register is determined to naming and shaming all sex offenders. The first national sexual offenders register was launched in November 2019. It contains the database of those convicted for sexual violence since 2015 – an important step towards clamping down on abuse. However, for complaints on rape, child abuse, or domestic violence call any of the following numbers 08175899289, 09062887858, 09062887856, 09062887849, 09062887841, 09062887870, 08023532283, 09062887864, 09062887861 and 09062887860. Source By Aderogba George Abuja - The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP)on Monday launched the sex offenders register to curb sexual violence in the country. The register is a way of documenting names of sexual violence culprits after they have been prosecuted andfound guilty of the… November 25, 2019 In "News" Enugu- Participants at a one-day stakeholders summit on Violence Against Persons Prohibition (VAPP) Bill on Tuesday advocated a jail term without option of fine for convicted rapists in Enugu State. This was part of the resolutions of the summit organised by the Women’s Aid Collective (WACOL), a non-governmental organisation in… December 3, 2014 In "Health" By Ikenna Uwadileke   Abuja   -     The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP), says it will establish sexual offenders’ register as part of measures to check gender- ba